        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cli): handle Bun optional import misses",
        "body": "Fixes #86198\n\n## Summary\n- Recognize Bun-style direct module-miss messages in the launcher optional-import guard.\n- Keep Node direct misses supported through `ERR_MODULE_NOT_FOUND`, URL, and absolute-path checks.\n- Preserve the transitive-miss behavior so missing dependencies from `dist/entry.js` are still surfaced instead of being treated as missing OpenClaw build output.\n\n## Verification\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs --config test/vitest/vitest.e2e.config.ts test/openclaw-launcher.e2e.test.ts --reporter=dot` -> 23 tests passed\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check openclaw.mjs test/openclaw-launcher.e2e.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `./node_modules/.bin/oxlint --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.core.json openclaw.mjs test/openclaw-launcher.e2e.test.ts`\n\n## Live Bun proof\n- Head tested: `41b07bb21f83a71a73573fffa5272dd14755ef6b`\n- Environment: WSL Ubuntu-24.04 under `/root/src/openclaw-86198`, Bun `1.3.14`\n- Command shape: built temporary launcher fixtures that execute `openclaw.mjs` under Bun with one fixture where the optional `dist/entry.js` import is missing, and one fixture where `dist/entry.js` exists but imports a missing transitive dependency.\n- Result: the optional missing `dist/entry.js` case was skipped as intended and the launcher continued into the root help path; the transitive missing dependency from inside `dist/entry.js` still failed visibly instead of being swallowed.\n- Remaining gap: this proof exercises the affected launcher surface locally under Bun. It does not depend on hosted CI because the current CI failure observed on this PR is in an unrelated cron-service timing test.\n\nNote: commit is SSH-signed locally and verified with `git log --show-signature -1` after rebasing onto current `main`.",
